  "line_count": 705,
  "purpose": "`collections.vitl` is a public stdlib surface inside the `collections` family. It should be read as one focused slice of the broader family responsibility: Container and traversal surfaces such as vector, deque, queue, stack, linked list, hashmap, hashset, graph, and matrix.",
  "use_cases": [
    "A build report groups diagnostics in a vector and indexes them in a hashmap.",
    "A scheduler stores pending work in a queue or deque.",
    "A graph or matrix page should explain why those shapes exist, not just list filenames."
